      "skos:definition": {
        "@value": "error function",
        "@language": "en"
      },
      "skos:note": {
        "@value": "stem:[\"erf \"x = 2/(sqrt pi) int_0^x e^(-t^2) \"d\"t]\n\nstem:[\"erfc \" x = 1 - \"erf \"x] is called the complementary error function.\n\nIn statistics, the distribution function\n\nstem:[rm(Phi)(x) = 1/(sqrt(2pi)) int_(-oo)^x e^(-t^2//2)\"d\"t]\n\nis used.\n",
        "@language": "en"
      },
